  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">U-LEARN: Uganda Learning, Evidence, Accountability, and Research Network</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DFID is seeking a service provider (SP) to provide verification of partner deliverables, an enhanced capacity to provide and regularly champion accountability to affected people and develop, manage and promote a protracted crisis learning hub. This will be required for the lifetime of the Building Resilience and an effective Emergency Refugee response (BRAER) programme. The grant will run for a three-year period, with a potential extension, and will deliver against three core outputs. U-LEARN will inform adaptive programming from the outset and will include annual periods of joint SP, DFID and partners&#x2019; review and reflection. It will have built in flexibility to deliver additional outputs as negotiated through periodic work plans to be agreed between the SP and DFID.</narrative>
  </description>
